# Planning Phase

When creating implementation plans:

## Be Skeptical & Interactive

- Question vague requirements; verify with code
- Don't write the full plan in one shot—get buy-in at each step
- Read all context files completely before planning
- No open questions in the final plan—resolve before finalizing

## Plan Structure

Plans go in `thoughts/plans/` as `YYYY-MM-DD-description.md`

Each phase must include:
- **Automated Verification**: Commands to run (`make test`, `npm run lint`, etc.)
- **Manual Verification**: Steps requiring human testing

## Success Criteria Format

```markdown
#### Automated Verification:
- [ ] Tests pass: `make test`
- [ ] Lint passes: `make lint`

#### Manual Verification:
- [ ] Feature works as expected in UI
- [ ] Edge cases verified
```

## What We're NOT Doing

Explicitly list out-of-scope items to prevent scope creep.
